input_full.title: MCP tool: AskUserQuestion interaction analysis for self-improve
input_full.body:
MCP tool designed for use during the `/self-improve` skill. Scrapes archived sessions to extract all structured interactions where Claude asks the user a question (AskUserQuestion tool calls), along with surrounding context.

## Purpose

Surface patterns in how questions are asked, what the user chooses, and whether the outcomes were productive. Feed into self-improve Pillar 1 (user patterns) and Pillar 3 (planning quality).

## Capabilities

- **Extract** all AskUserQuestion invocations from archive entries, including:
  - The question text and options presented
  - The user's selected answer(s)
  - Surrounding context (what triggered the question, what happened after)
  - Skill/substate at time of question
- **Report generation** formatted for both LLM consumption and human review
- **Statistics:** frequency by skill, option selection distribution, question categories
- **Range controls:** filter by date range, epoch, skill type, entry ID range

## Proposed Tools

- `sbs_question_analysis(since?, until?, skill?, limit?)` - Main analysis report
- `sbs_question_stats(since?, until?)` - Aggregate statistics only
